ial%2Bchange%26talk%3Dlee_smolin_on_science_and_democracy%26year%3D2003&env=vp&gdfp_req=1&impl=s&iu=%2F5641%2Fmobile%2Fios%2Fweb&output=xml_vast2&sz=640x360&unviewed_position_start=1&url=%5Breferrer%5D"}}, "canonical": "https://www.ted.com/talks/lee_smolin_on_science_and_democracy"}], "hero_load": "https://pi.tedcdn.com/r/pe.tedcdn.com/images/ted/58247_640x480.jpg?q=50&w=15", "duration": 745, "id": 394, "ratings": [{"count": 68, "id": 24, "name": "Persuasive"}, {"count": 92, "id": 8, "name": "Informative"}, {"count": 73, "id": 22, "name": "Fascinating"}, {"count": 65, "id": 21, "name": "Unconvincing"}, {"count": 61, "id": 25, "name": "OK"}, {"count": 40, "id": 2, "name": "Confusing"}, {"count": 42, "id": 11, "name": "Longwinded"}, {"count": 32, "id": 9, "name": "Ingenious"}, {"count": 42, "id": 10, "name": "Inspiring"}, {"count": 10, "id": 7, "name": "Funny"}, {"count": 12, "id": 3, "name": "Courageous"}, {"count": 9, "id": 26, "name": "Obnoxious"}, {"count": 10, "id": 23, "name": "Jaw-dropping"}, {"count": 6, "id": 1, "name": "Beautiful"}], "speakers": [{"description": "Physicist", "firstname": "Lee", "title": "", "lastname": "Smolin", "middleinitial": "", "whylisten": "<p>Lee Smolin&#39;s bachelor&#39;s degree was in physics and philosophy -- twin passions that have complemented one another throughout his blazing career as a theoretical physicist. As <a href=\\"http://www.thetroublewithphysics.com/brief%20bio.html\\" target=\\"_blank\\">his website bio</a>  is careful to state, &quot;<strong>His main contributions to research <em>so far</em> are to the field of quantum gravity.</strong>&quot; He&#39;s made contributions in many other fields, including cosmology, quantum mechanics, elementary particle physics and theoretical biology, and is the author of (among other books) <a href=\\"http://www.thetroublewithphysics.com/\\" target=\\"_blank\\"><em>The Trouble With Physics</em></a>, a work that questions the very basis of the prevailing string theory.</p><p>Taking 